Remarks were made by Vice President Mike Pence at the House and Senate retreat in West Virginia. Pence expressed his condolences for those involved in a train accident earlier in the day and thanked the first responders. He then praised the accomplishments of the conservative agenda in the past year, including tax cuts, deregulation, and military spending. Pence encouraged the attendees to continue telling the story of these accomplishments and to focus on the upcoming midterms. He also highlighted the positive impact of the tax cuts on working families. Pence concluded by expressing his faith in the Republican majority and in the American people, and he called for unity and continued service to the nation.